    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-09T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-09T06:00:00-05:00" n="56"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.96/332</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-09T11:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6.17 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1124. For War Trade Board:</p>
                <p>Does vessel from Spain to America via Panama Canal, not stopping at Canal ports,
                    have to subject itself to jurisdiction of Board? If so, what must owners do?
                    Please instruct. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1"
                        >Chadbourne</persName>.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
